727076f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, between 201st and 202nd Streets, showing in a set of three views the William McCrum house from 1891 to 1896.  The Cortlandt Realty Company owned it in 1913, having purchased it from Mrs. Belnap.  In 1922 Alonzo D. Frisco was the occupant.  He manufactured cement blocks.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
